HEADWORD: Unabsorbable
<hw>Un`ab*sorb"a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Not absorbable; specifically <fld>(Physiol.)</fld>, not capable of absorption; unable to pass by osmosis into the circulating blood; <as>as, the <ex>unabsorbable</ex> portion of food</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unacceptability</ent>⟦br⟧
